This audit logs were analyzed using the `aureport` tool, which is part of the Linux Audit framework.

> üîß Command used to generate this summary:
> ```bash
> sudo aureport --summary -if audit.log
> ```

### üìä Summary Report Output

| Metric                            | Count  | Notes                                                       |
|----------------------------------|--------|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| üîê Failed Login Attempts         | 87     | Indicates brute-force or credential stuffing attack        |
| üîì Successful Logins             | 1      | Only one login succeeded ‚Äì likely the initial compromise   |
| ‚ùå Failed Authentications        | 89     | Suggests multiple failed sudo or privilege escalation tries |
| ‚úÖ Successful Authentications    | 3      | Could indicate attacker's privilege escalation success      |
