üß† Analysis
There were 87 failed login attempts within a 6-minute period.
The same IP address (192.168.4.155) repeatedly attempted to authenticate using SSH.
A single successful login eventually occurred after all failed ones.
This behavior ‚Äî a high number of failed login attempts followed by a successful login from the same source ‚Äî is characteristic of a brute-force attack, where the attacker tries many combinations to guess valid credentials.




üîç What is the attacker's IP address?
> üîß Command used
> sudo aureport --summary --host -if audit.log

Host Summary Report
